{"title": "China's love affair with property not over despite downturn", "tags": "business", "timestamp": "2022-09-05", "content": "SINGAPORE - Real estate ownership is widely viewed the world over as a good way to grow generational wealth.\nIn China, this love affair with property is particularly entrenched. Amid a dearth of investment alternatives onshore, housing assets account for a staggering 70 per cent of urban family wealth as at 2019."}